def get_imdb_rating(movie_title=None):
    connection_retry=1
    if movie_title==None:
        return None, None, None
    else:
#         print(f'searching imdb {movie_title}')
        while connection_retry==1:
            try:
                html_content = requests.get(f'https://www.imdb.com/find?q={urllib.parse.quote(movie_title)}').text
                connection_retry=0
            except ConnectionError or SSLError:
                continue                
        
        try:
            soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, "html5lib")
            table = soup.find("table", attrs={"class": "findList"})
            
            if table != None:
                rows = table.find_all('tr')
                if rows != None:
                    cols = rows[0].find_all('td')
                    if cols != None:
                        ele = cols[0]
#                         print('scraping imdb rating')
                        html_content = requests.get('https://www.imdb.com{}'.format(ele.a['href'])).text
                        soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, "html5lib")
                        div = soup.find("div", attrs={"class": "ratingValue"})

                        rating = float(re.findall('^\d+.\d|^\d+', 
                                                  div.strong.get('title'))[0])
                        num_user_rates = int(re.search('(\d+(,\d{3})+)|(\d+) user', 
                                                       div.strong.get('title'))[0].replace(',','').replace(' user',''))
#                         print('done!')
            
#             time.sleep(1) #to prevent 1ratelimit
#             clear_output(wait=True)
            return rating, num_user_rates, ele.a['href']
        except:
            return None, None, None

def percentile(n):
    def percentile_(x):
        return x.quantile(n)
    percentile_.__name__ = 'percentile_{:2.0f}'.format(n*100)
    return percentile_

# Movie / TV Show recommender based on title, description, cast, director & genre 
df['feature_join'] = (df['title'].map(str) + ' ' +
df['description'].map(str) + ' ' +
#  df['country_list'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x)) + ' ' +
df['cast_list'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x)) + ' ' +
df['director_list'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x)) + ' ' +
df['listed_in_list'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x)) )

# remove numbers & punctuation & special characters
df['feature_join'] = df['feature_join'].apply(lambda x: re.sub(r'\d+', '', re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', x.lower())))
# remove short words
df['feature_join'] = df['feature_join'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join([w for w in x.split() if len(w)>3]))

# tokenize words
df['feature_join_token'] = df['feature_join'].apply(lambda x: word_tokenize(x))

# remove stopwords
df['feature_join_clean'] = df['feature_join_token'].apply(lambda x: [word for word in x if not word in set(stopwords.words('english'))])

# stemming
snowball = SnowballStemmer(language = 'english')
df['feature_join_stem'] = df['feature_join_clean'].apply(lambda x: [snowball.stem(word) for word in x])


# lemmatization
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
df['feature_join_pos'] = df['feature_join_clean'].apply(lambda x: ['n' if tag.startswith('NN') else 'v' if tag.startswith('VB') else 'a'
                                  for word, tag in pos_tag(x)])
df['feature_join_lemma'] = df.apply(lambda x: [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word,pos) for word, pos in 
                                             zip(x['feature_join_clean'], x['feature_join_pos']) ], axis=1)

# combine tokens
df['feature_join_clean'] = df['feature_join_clean'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x))
df['feature_join_stem'] = df['feature_join_stem'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x))
df['feature_join_lemma'] = df['feature_join_lemma'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x))



    













In [19]:



    


cosine_similarities = {}

df_recomm = df.copy()[['title','type','feature_join_clean']]
df_recomm['title'] = df_recomm['title'].str.lower()
df_recomm['titles'] = df_recomm['title']
df_recomm.set_index('titles', inplace = True)
df_recomm['index_no'] = np.arange(len(df_recomm))
tf = TfidfVectorizer(analyzer='word', ngram_range=(1, 3), min_df=0, stop_words='english')
tfidf_matrix = tf.fit_transform(df_recomm['feature_join_clean'])
cosine_similarities['all'] = linear_kernel(tfidf_matrix, tfidf_matrix)
tv_tfidf_matrix = tf.fit_transform(df_recomm.query("type!='Movie'")['feature_join_clean'])
cosine_similarities['TV Show'] = linear_kernel(tv_tfidf_matrix, tv_tfidf_matrix)
movie_tfidf_matrix = tf.fit_transform(df_recomm.query("type=='Movie'")['feature_join_clean'])
cosine_similarities['Movie'] = linear_kernel(movie_tfidf_matrix, movie_tfidf_matrix)

def recommendations(name, cosine_similarities, recom_df, types='all'):
    if name=='':
        return 'Please select movie/tv show'
    
    if types=='all':
        recom_df = recom_df.copy()
    elif types!='all' and types in ('Movie', 'TV Show'):
        recom_df = recom_df.query("type==@types").copy()
        recom_df['index_no'] = np.arange(len(recom_df))
    else:
        return 'Please select specify type'

    
    if name not in recom_df.index:
        name = process.extract(name, recom_df.index)
        if len(name)>=1:
            print('fuzzy matched', name[0])
            name = name[0][0]
        else:
            return 'Please try another movie or TV show.'
    
    top5_recomm = []    
    # gettin the index of the movie/tv show that matches 
    score_series = pd.Series(cosine_similarities[types][recom_df.index.get_loc(name.lower())])    
    # sort scores by highest similarity
    score_series = score_series.sort_values(ascending=False)
    # select top 5 similarity without first(=exact match)
    for i in score_series[1:6].index:
        top5_recomm.append(recom_df.index[i])
    return top5_recomm
